Yes it was version 0.6 as it says in the download section of tensorflow,
but i don't know how to install the master version as a package, should I
download the github repository on the library folder (
/Library/Python/2.7/site-packages/tensorflow/...) ?
Thanks a lot,
Manu

On Mon, Jan 18, 2016 at 3:30 PM, Aymeric Damien notifications@github.com
wrote:

What is your tensorflow version? You might need master branch version of
tensorflow to make that script running. (In 0.6.0, ExponentialMovingAverage
has no attributes variables_to_restore, but master version has it.)
